{"name": "pybottrader", "metadata": {"name": "pybottrader", "version": "0.0.4", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["attrs", "pandas", "yfinance"], "summary": "An experimental Python library to implement trading bots", "upload_time": 1733632725}, "documentation": ["# PyBotTrader\n\nVersion 0.0.4\n\nAPI Documentation <https://jailop.github.io/pybottrader/pybottrader.html>\n\nAn experimental Python library to implement trading bots. I'm building this\nlibrary based on patterns I've observed implementing trading algorithms for my\nclients. It is intended, when it becomes stable, to be used by retail traders.\n\nFeatures:\n\n- Financial indicators for streaming data. They don\u00b4t make calculations from\n  scratch but instead by keeping memory of previous results (intended to be use\n  with real time data). An `update` method is used to push new data and update\n  their results. They use a bracket notation to bring access to results, like\n  `ind[0]` for the most recent result and `ind[-1]` for the previous one.\n  Current implemented indicators are `MA` (simple moving average), `EMA`\n  (exponential moving average), RSI (Relative Strength Index), MACD (Moving\n  average convergence/divergence), and `ROI` (return of investment). Check some\n  examples in [this test\n  file](https://github.com/jailop/pybottrader/blob/main/test/test_indicators.py).\n- Data streamers to read or retrieve sequential data. They provide a `next`\n  method to bring access to the next data item. Current data streamers\n  implemented: `CSVFileStreamer` and `YFinanceStreamer` (based on the `yfinace`\n  library.)\n- Portfolio managers, to implement buy/sell policies and deliver orders.\n  Currently only a `DummyPortfolio` is implemented, one that when receives a\n  `buy` signal buys everything that it can with its available cash, and sells\n  all its assets when receives a `sell` signal. This portfolio can be used for\n  back-testing.\n- A strategy model, so the user of this library can implement it owns strategies\n  (this is the purpose of this library).  A strategy is built to consume a data\n  stream, compute indicators, and produce BUY/SELL signals.\n- Traders, these are bots that based on a data stream, a strategy, and a\n  portfolio, run the trading operations. Currently only a basic Trader is\n  offered, useful for back-testing.\n\nUsing this library looks like:\n\n``` python\nfrom pybottrader.indicators import RSI\nfrom pybottrader.datastreamers import YFinanceStreamer\nfrom pybottrader.portfolios import DummyPortfolio\nfrom pybottrader.traders import Trader\nfrom pybottrader.strategies import Strategy, Position\n\nclass SimpleRSIStrategy(Strategy):\n    rsi: RSI\n    last_flip = Position.SELL\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.rsi = RSI()\n\n    def evaluate(self, *args, **kwargs) -> Position:\n        # default positio STAY\n        position = Position.STAY\n        # It is expected that open and close values\n        # are provided by the data streamer. Otherwise,\n        # just return the default position (STAY)\n        if \"open\" not in kwargs or \"close\" not in kwargs:\n            return position\n        # Update the RSI indicator\n        self.rsi.update(open_price=kwargs[\"open\"], close_price=kwargs[\"close\"])\n        # If RSI is less than 30, buy\n        if self.last_flip == Position.SELL and self.rsi[0] < 30:\n            position = Position.BUY\n            self.last_flip = Position.BUY\n        # If RSI is greater than 70, sell\n        elif self.last_flip == Position.BUY and self.rsi[0] > 70:\n            position = Position.SELL\n            self.last_flip = Position.SELL\n        return position\n\n# Apple, daily data from 2021 to 2023\ndatastream = YFinanceStreamer(\"AAPL\", start=\"2021-01-01\", end=\"2023-12-31\")\n# Start with USD 1,000\nportfolio = DummyPortfolio(1000)\n# My strategy\nstrategy = SimpleRSIStrategy()\n# Putting everything together\ntrader = Trader(strategy, portfolio, datastream)\n\n# A nice header\nprint(\n    \"{:10} {:4} {:>10} {:>10}  {:>10} {:>10}\".format(\n        \"Date\", \"Pos.\", \"Price\", \"ROI\", \"Valuation\", \"Accum.ROI\"\n    )\n)\n\n# Run the back-testing\nwhile trader.next():\n    status = trader.status()\n    if status.position != Position.STAY:\n        date = status.time.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n        # A nice output\n        print(\n            f\"{date} {status.position.name:4} {status.data['close']:10.2f} \"\n            + f\"{status.roi * 100.0:10.2f}% {status.portfolio_value:10.2f} \"\n            + f\"{status.accumulated_roi * 100.0:10.2f}%\"\n        )\n```\n\nOutput is shown below. Using this strategy ended in a loss.\n\n```\nDate       Pos.      Price        ROI   Valuation  Accum.ROI\n2021-02-10 BUY      132.59       0.00%    1000.00       0.00%\n2021-04-09 SELL     130.25      -1.77%     982.35      -1.77%\n2021-05-05 BUY      125.45       0.00%     982.35      -1.77%\n2021-06-21 SELL     129.78       3.45%    1016.28       1.63%\n2021-09-20 BUY      140.43      -0.00%    1016.28       1.63%\n2021-10-20 SELL     146.64       4.42%    1061.21       6.12%\n2022-01-24 BUY      159.02       0.00%    1061.21       6.12%\n2022-03-25 SELL     172.12       8.24%    1148.69      14.87%\n2022-04-25 BUY      160.46       0.00%    1148.69      14.87%\n2022-06-08 SELL     145.98      -9.03%    1045.00       4.50%\n2022-09-02 BUY      153.93       0.00%    1045.00       4.50%\n2023-01-24 SELL     141.05      -8.37%     957.52      -4.25%\n2023-08-04 BUY      180.62       0.00%     957.52      -4.25%\n2023-10-10 SELL     177.29      -1.85%     939.85      -6.02%\n```\n\nShortly, I'm going to release more documentation and more examples.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pybottrader.traders", "documentation": ["A collection of bottraders"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pybottrader.traders.Trader", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "pybottrader.traders.Trader.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "strategy", "type": {"name": "Strategy", "xref": {"fqname": "pybottrader.traders.strategies.Strategy", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "portfolio", "type": {"name": "Portfolio", "xref": {"fqname": "pybottrader.traders.portfolios.Portfolio", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "datastream", "type": {"name": "DataStreamer", "xref": {"fqname": "pybottrader.traders.datastreamers.DataStreamer", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Init method"]}, {"name": "pybottrader.traders.Trader.next", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.traders.Trader.status", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "StreamIteration", "xref": {"fqname": "pybottrader.traders.datastreamers.StreamIteration", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Trader last result"]}, {"name": "pybottrader.traders.Trader.run", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "pybottrader.traders.Trader.portfolio", "type": {"name": "Portfolio", "xref": {"fqname": "pybottrader.traders.portfolios.Portfolio", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.traders.Trader.datastream", "type": {"name": "DataStreamer", "xref": {"fqname": "pybottrader.traders.datastreamers.DataStreamer", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.traders.Trader.strategy", "type": {"name": "Strategy", "xref": {"fqname": "pybottrader.traders.strategies.Strategy", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.traders.Trader.last_result", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "StreamIteration", "xref": {"fqname": "pybottrader.traders.datastreamers.StreamIteration", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.traders.Trader.last_valuation", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Base class"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators", "documentation": ["Moving Average\nImplementation adopted from:\nhttps://github.com/jailop/trading/tree/main/indicators-c++"], "functions": [{"name": "pybottrader.indicators.roi", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "initial_value", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "final_value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return on investment"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pybottrader.indicators.Indicator", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "pybottrader.indicators.Indicator.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mem_size", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["@param mem_size: The size of the memory buffer. The\n    default value is 1."]}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.Indicator.__getitem__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["@param key: 0 for the most recent update\n            a negative number for the n-previous updates\n\nA negative number less than -mem_size returns NAN.\nA positive number returns NAN."]}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.Indicator.push", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Stores in the buffer `value` as the more recent update.\nIn the current implementation, a ring buffer is used\nto save these values.\n\n@param value: The most recent update"]}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.Indicator.get", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["The same as `__getitem__`"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "pybottrader.indicators.Indicator.mem_pos", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.Indicator.mem_data", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.Indicator.mem_size", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Base class to build indicators. It provides a buffer to\nkeep the last `mem_size` values and functions to push\nnew values and retrieve using bracket notation or the\nfunction get.\n\nAll derived classes, call the __init__ method of this class\nand when an update ocurrs, they push the new value\ninto the memory buffer.\n\nBecause this class is intended to be used for time series,\nindices go backwards, being `0` the last updated value, -1\nthe previous one, -2 the previous of the previos one...\nIf a value is requested with a positive index or a negative\nindex which absolute values is greater than `mem_size`, then\nan NAN value is returned."]}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.MA", "bases": ["Indicator"], "methods": [{"name": "pybottrader.indicators.MA.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "period", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["The number of period or window size is required to initialize a MA\nobject."]}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.MA.update", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Aggregate a new value into the moving average"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "pybottrader.indicators.MA.period", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.MA.prevs", "type": {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.MA.length", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.MA.pos", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.MA.accum", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Moving Average"]}, {"name": "pybottrader.indicators.EMA", "bases": ["Indicator"], "methods": [{"name": "pybottrader.